==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gynandromorphism
<hw>Gy*nan`dro*mor"phism</hw>
<pr>(j⟦icr⟧*n⟦acr⟧n`dr⟦osl⟧*m⟦ocir⟧r"f⟦icr⟧z'm)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>gynh`</grk> a woman, female + <grk>'anh`r</grk>,
<grk>'andro`s</grk>, a man, male + <grk>morfh`</grk> form.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An abnormal condition of certain animals, in
which one side has the external characters of the male, and the other
those of the female.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gynandromorphous</ent>⟦br⟧
